      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask the new patient for their email address.\n\nSay something like: \"Since this is your first visit, \nwe'll need a couple of extra details. First — what's \nthe best email address for you? We'll use it to send \nyou intake forms and set up your patient portal.\"\n\nIf the user gives an email, read it back to confirm: \n\"Just to make sure — that's [email], correct?\" Spell \nout anything ambiguous (e.g. \"That's J-O-H-N at \ngmail dot com?\").\n\nIf the email sounds wrong (no \"at\" symbol, clearly \nincomplete): \"Hmm, that doesn't sound quite right — \ncould you say it one more time?\"\n\nIf the user says they don't have email: \"No problem \n— we can send the forms by mail or have them ready \nfor you when you arrive. We'll skip that for now.\"\n\nIf the user doesn't want to provide it: \"I understand \n— we just use it for intake forms and portal access. \nNothing promotional. But if you'd rather not, we can \nhandle the paperwork in person.\"\n\nDo NOT ask more than twice."
      }
    },
